🔹 Avoid anti-patterns
for i in range(len(arr)) when you don’t need the index
Nested loops when a linear pass works
🧠 2) Loop Complexity Awareness
Single loop → O(n)
Nested loops → often O(n²)
Early exit can reduce average time
Prefer one-pass solutions when possible
🧠 3) Sliding Window (CORE DSA)
🔹 Idea

Maintain a running window instead of recomputing.

🔹 Fixed-size window
Track sum/count for window size k
Update by:
add new element
remove outgoing element
🔹 When to use
“subarray of size k”
“max/min over contiguous segment”
“count/avg over window”
🔹 Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)
